    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><font face="Arial" color='Black'><br>Changing the "K-frame" (crossmember), is a big deal, but if your current mounts are welded down, you may have to. There are two types of motor mounts used in an A-body, the first I call "Flat plate" style, and are used on 273 & 318 cars up to about '72. The second, which we will call "Through bolt" style, are used on 360 and larger installations, and on all cars '73 and later. This info comes from the best info I can find and personal experience. In putting a 360 in my car, I discovered the "ears" on the block have a different offset on the Left/Drivers side. You can buy the correct mounts for the conversion in National Dragster, I've seen them advertised, or modify yours (like I did). If you have not moved the motor forward or back, it's likely you won't have problems with the tranny X-member or prop-shaft, especially if your "Redneck" friends did a weld job on the motor mounts. They likely did not take the time to change the motor set-back, as this plays hell with everything like steering linkage and tranny shifter, etc. As far as you cocked to one side problem try this: Check to see if you have the flat plate style mounts down there, take a 3/4" socket and reach up from the ground, loosen the bolts on each side then use a floor jack and a 2x4" to keep from denting the oilpan, you can straighten the motor out, and re-torque the mount bolts.<BR><BR>On to sagging suspension, Have you tightened up the torsion bars? You can just tighten 'em up, and bounce/roll the car a bit till it sets level with the rear diff sitting on a floor jack. If they are totally hosed, Mopar performance has several replacement torsion bars to choose from. They are described by car weight, but take note: some B-Body guys run a lightweight A-body bar tightened WAY up to help give the car a quicker reaction time. I havn't played with this, ask Jeff Kotulak @ Mopar Techline for his suggestions, he will treat you right.<BR><BR>These were not stupid questions, but serious questions about important stuff! So don't feel weird asking! Hope this Helps! <BR><BR>XE Ryder</td>
    </tr>

